  "text": "In this paper, we utilize the partial nulling concept to ease the perfect nulling condition. The partial nulling has been previously proposed by the authors to exploit the receiver's capability of spatial filtering for lUI cancellation and thus to enable the increase in degrees of freedom at the trans mitter [CITATION_1] . The idea minimizing signal-to-Ieakage-plus-noise ratio (SLNR) also eases the perfect nulling condition [CITATION_2] , [11] . However, the SLNR-based beamforming considers the lUI power only. Thus, the degrees of freedom required to cancel the lUI at the receiver side is not controllable in spite of low lUI power. Our base concept is rather similar to coordinated beamforming [12] . However, our proposal can determine the transmit weight matrix uniquely without any iterative procedures.",
